Run Vector Searches Using Query API

Use Query API to run vector searches in Data Cloud. Use these examples as starting points.

EXAMPLE

Use this syntax to run a vector search.

SELECT * from vector_search(TABLE(<Your
     Vector_Embedding DMO>), '<Search String>'), '<PreFilteringColumn><Operator>"<Value>"', '<k=topK results>')

Where:

<Your Vector_Embedding DMO> is the API name of the index DMO.
<Search String> is the search string for the vector search.
<PreFilteringColumn> is a boolean expression that filters the scalar fields or the primary key field, so you can limit your search with certain conditions. When multiple prefiltering conditions are used, they are combined with the logical AND operator.
<k=topK results> is the number of most similar results to return.

Use this syntax to run a vector search that joins a index DMO with a chunk DMO.

SELECT v.score__c Score__c, c.chunk__c Chunk__c from vector_search(TABLE(<Your Vector_Embedding DMO>), '<Search String>', ‘language=English, status=active’, 10) v join <Your Chunk DMO> c on v.RecordId__c = c.Record__c order by 1 limit 10

Where:

<Your Vector_Embedding DMO> is a string that represents the object API name of the index DMO.
<Search String> is the search string for the vector search.
language=English, status=active is an example of a prefiltering condition that includes two filters. These filters are combined with the logical AND operator.
10 is the limit of results from the vector search.
<Your Chunk DMO> is the API name of your chunk DMO.
score__c is the similarity score of each vector to the input search string.
chunk__c is the chunk that was used to generate the vector embedding.

Use this syntax to run a vector search that joins a vector DMO with a chunk DMO and a file entry for the UDMO.

SELECT v.score__c Score__c, c.chunk__c Chunk__c, u.FilePath__c FilePath__c from vector_search(TABLE(<Your Vector_Embedding DMO>), '<Search String>','',10) v join <Your Chunk DMO>' on v.RecordId__c = c.Record__c join <Your UDMO> u on c.SourceRecordId__c = u.FilePath order by 1 desc limit 10

Where:

<Your Vector_Embedding DMO> is a string that represents the name of the index DMO.
<Search String> is the search string for the vector search.
<Your Chunk DMO> - is the API name of the chunk DMO that contains the chunks from which the vector embeddings were created.
<Your UDMO> - is the API name of the UDMO from which the chunks were created.
score__c is the similarity score of each vector to the input search string.
chunk__c is the chunk that was used to generate the vector embedding.
filePath__C is the relative path of each file that was used to create the chunks and vector embeddings.

Use this syntax to run a vector search that uses and and or operators to join multiple filtering conditions.

(select * from ((select * from (vector_search(TABLE(<Your Vector_Embedding DMO>),'<Search String>','strField1 != ''v1'' and strField2 = ''v2'' and (strField3 = ''v3'' or strField4 not in (''a'', ''b'', ''c'') or strField5 in (''a'', ''b'', ''c'')) and strField6=''v6''', 10)))) offset 0 limit 50000);

Where:

<Your Vector_Embedding DMO> is a string that represents the name of the index DMO.
<Search String> is the search string for the vector search.
The logical and operator is used to retrieve records that meet all conditions, the logical or operator is used to retrieve records that meet any condition, and the in operator is used to retrieve records where the value of the field is one of the enumerated values.
Vector Search Query Pre-Filtering
Enhance your vector search queries with pre-filtering fields. Use logical operators and manage case sensitivity for field names and values to ensure precise data retrieval.
